SIMPLE: elliptical
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Elliptical
<hw>El*lip"tic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/: cf. F.
<ets>elliptique</ets>. See <er>Ellipsis</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of
or pertaining to an ellipse; having the form of an ellipse; oblong, with
rounded ends.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The planets move in <qex>elliptic</qex> orbits.</q>
<rj><qau>Cheyne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The billiard sharp who any one catches,⟦br⟧
His doom's extremely hard --⟦br⟧
He's made to dwell⟦br⟧
In a dungeon cell⟦br⟧
On a spot that's always barred.⟦br⟧
And there he plays extravagant matches⟦br⟧
In fitless finger-stalls⟦br⟧
On a cloth untrue⟦br⟧
With a twisted cue⟦br⟧
And <qex>elliptical</qex> billiard balls!</q>⟦br⟧
<rj><qau>Gilbert and Sullivan (The Mikado: The More Humane Mikado
Song)</qau></rj></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having a part omitted; <as>as, an
<ex>elliptical</ex> phrase</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>leaving out information essential to comprehension;
so concise as to be difficult to understand; obscure or ambiguous; -- of
speech or writing; <as>as, an <ex>elliptical</ex>
comment</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Elliptic chuck</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Chuck</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Elliptic compasses</b></col>, <cd>an
instrument arranged for drawing ellipses.</cd> -- <col><b>Elliptic
function</b></col>. <fld>(Math.)</fld> <cd>See <er>Function</er>.</cd>
-- <col><b>Elliptic integral</b></col>. <fld>(Math.)</fld> <cd>See
<er>Integral</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Elliptic polarization</b></col>.
<cd>See under <er>Polarization</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elliptically</ent>⟦br⟧
